            "summary": "Dollar Tree Inc. (DLTR) shares surged following the report of strong same-store sales figures, amidst a positive earnings season. Analyst Matthew Boss from JPMorgan upgraded the rating from Neutral to Overweight, setting a new price target of $111, up from $72. Dollar Tree posted a same-store sales growth of 5.4%, surpassing the consensus of 4.1%. Both ticket and traffic showed strength, with a 2.5% increase in traffic, notably attracting more consumers with a household income exceeding $100,000. Additionally, higher-purchase-frequency customers rose by 9% year-on-year. Ticket comp growth of +2.8% was supported by a variety of price points and strong demand in seasonal and discretionary categories. Management hinted that the second-quarter same-store sales growth could be at the higher end of expectations. For more details, visit the full article on Benzinga.com.",
